Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_set_sca...egative_delays(25.10)  timing_set_sca...egative_delays(25.10)

Name
       timing_set_scaling_for_negative_delays

Syntax
        timing_set_scaling_for_negative_delays

       {default | divider | multiplier}

       Default: default

       Modifies the scaling of the negative delay value to be used during tim-
       ing analysis. This variable does not affect the positive delay.

       When  set  to default, the derated check/delay = negative check/delay *
       (2.0 - derating factor), where the derating factor is  the  value  that
       you set using the set_timing_derate command.

       When  set  to divider, divides the negative delay value by the derating
       factor. When set to multiplier, multiplies the negative delay value  by
       the derating factor.

       Currently, constraints are used during timing in the flattened mode, so
       the  internal  ILM  instances  are  seen instead of the LEF pins of the
       ILMs. Therefore, reading the bounding  box  constraints  causes  errors
       without  this variable set. Notice that if you want to see the LEF pins
       of the ILM in GUI, the design must be in the unflattened mode.

       To set this global variable, use the set_global command.

